Name: Elm Creek Park Reserve Entrance
Notes: Entrance identified as transit friendly, but bring your bike!  This entrance sits about 3 miles from the commuter train NSSC reccommends for accessing this park.

Name: Springbrook Nature Center Entrance
Notes: This entrance is about 0.6 miles from the bus stop NSSC identifies as a good option for accessing this park.

Name: Golden Valley Rd & Theodore Wirth Pkwy Entrance
Notes: Take Bus 14 to reach this entrance.

Name: Wirth Chalet & Theodore Wirth Pkwy Entrance
Notes: Take Bus 7 to reach this entrance.

Name: Wayzata Blvd N & Theodore Wirth Pkwy Entrance
Notes: Take Bus 9 to reach this entrance.

Name: Richfield Rd & Wm Berry Rd Entrance
Notes: Take Bus 6 to reach this entrance.

Name: 50th St W & Minnehaha Parkway Entrance
Notes: Take buses 4 or 6 to reach this stop. This is the southernmost access to the Minneapolis Chain of Lakes, stopping just south of Lake Harriet.

Name: Hyland Lake Park Reserve Entrance
Notes: Sits about 0.6 miles from the Normandale Blvd & Poplar Bridge Rd bus stop.

Name: MN Valley National Wildlife Refuge Entrance (Bass Ponds)
Notes: Enter here for the best access to the Bass Ponds.  Take the MOA stop on the Hiawatha LRT or the 539 bus to 86th and Old Shakopee Rd.

Name: MN Valley National Wildlife Refuge Entrance (Visitor Center)
Notes: Enter here for the best access to the Visitor Center.  Take the American Blvd stop on the Hiawatha LRT.

Name: Lebanon Hills Regional Park Entrance
Notes: Access via the Johnny Cake Ridge Rd stop.

Name: Minnesota River Valley Wildlife Refuge Visitors Center Entrances
